OL,3,CWelsh Government-owned Powys farm now
OL,4,Cworth half a million pounds less
OL,6,FBut the Senedd's Public Accounts and
OL,7,FPublic Administration committee has
OL,8,Ffound what it calls "signifiant
OL,9,Ffailings in the handling of the
OL,10,Facquisition".
OL,12,FThe committee's report says that the
OL,13,Fpurchase was "rushed" because of end-
OL,14,Fof-year budget pressures. It says the
OL,15,Fproperty, which is still owned by the
OL,16,FWelsh Government but run as a working
OL,17,Ffarm, is now worth half a million
OL,18,Fpounds less than its value in 2022.
