OL,3,CWelsh Government-owned Powys farm now
OL,4,Cworth half a million pounds less
OL,6,F"The arrival of the ospreys
OL,7,Fnecessarily impacted on the planned
OL,8,Fuse of the farm, and the original
OL,9,Fproject had to be stopped. Gilestone
OL,10,Fremains one of the Welsh Government's
OL,11,Fproperty assets, and is being managed
OL,12,Fon our behalf as a working farm. We
OL,13,Fcontinue to explore potential
OL,14,Fopportunities for its future use, in
OL,15,Fkeeping with our commitment to seek a
OL,16,Fsustainable outcome that helps local
OL,17,Fcommunities thrive.
OL,19,F"We will read the Committee's report
OL,20,Fwith interest, and respond in due
OL,21,Fcourse."
